message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper deals with adapting neural paragraph-level question answering models to the case where entire documents are given as input. This involves techniques from natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval, which are all relevant to the sub-categories listed. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) deals with natural language processing, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) deal with machine learning, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) deals with retrieving relevant information from large datasets, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) deals with neural networks.
